<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1436,152,498]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis box="[198,310,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Remarks:</emphasis>
Only two species have been described in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[844,967,312,338]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="61" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Londono-Mesa, 2003" authorityName=", Londono-Mesa" authorityYear="2003" box="[979,1367,312,338]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Spinosphaera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="carrerai">
<emphasis box="[979,1105,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">S. carrerai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Londono-Mesa, M. H." box="[1112,1367,312,338]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="747 - 759" refId="ref63053" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. (2003) Revision of Spinosphaera and establishment of the new genus Hutchingsiella (Polychaeta: Terebellidae: Terebellinae). Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 83, 747 - 759." type="journal article" year="2003">Londoño-Mesa, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the southern Mexican 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[424,547,352,378]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="61" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Londono-Mesa, 2003" authorityName="Londono-Mesa" authorityYear="2003" box="[617,1062,352,378]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Spinosphaera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hutchingsae">
<emphasis box="[617,792,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">S. hutchingsae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Londono-Mesa, M. H." box="[804,1062,352,378]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="747 - 759" refId="ref63053" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. (2003) Revision of Spinosphaera and establishment of the new genus Hutchingsiella (Polychaeta: Terebellidae: Terebellinae). Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 83, 747 - 759." type="journal article" year="2003">Londoño-Mesa, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Mexican 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1308,1432,352,378]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="61" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
. Since the genus has been recently revised (
<bibRefCitation author="Londono-Mesa, M. H." box="[656,912,392,418]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="747 - 759" refId="ref63053" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. (2003) Revision of Spinosphaera and establishment of the new genus Hutchingsiella (Polychaeta: Terebellidae: Terebellinae). Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 83, 747 - 759." type="journal article" year="2003">Londoño-Mesa, 2003</bibRefCitation>
) only a diagnosis is provided here. No additional specimens have been found of this genus, and thus both species are considered rare species in the region.
</paragraph>
